The '''[[2014–15 NHL season|2014–15]] [[Philadelphia Flyers]] [[season (sports)|season]]''' was the [[List of Philadelphia Flyers seasons|48th]] season for the [[National Hockey League]] franchise that was established on June 5, 1967.<ref>{{cite book |last=National Hockey League|title=The National Hockey League Official Guide & Record Book/2014|year=2013 |publisher= Diamond Sports Data, Inc. |page=101|isbn= 978-1-894801-26-3}}</ref> For the second time in three years, the Flyers failed to qualify for the playoffs.

==Off-season==
On April 15, 2014, the Flyers re-signed 27-year-old impending unrestricted [[free agent]] [[Andrew MacDonald (ice hockey)|Andrew MacDonald]] to a six-year extension for $30 million to keep the [[defenceman|defenseman]] under contract through the 2019–20 NHL season.<ref>https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/puck-daddy/flyers-give-andrew-macdonald-6-year---30-million-deal-145530186.html</ref>

On May 7, 2014, [[Paul Holmgren]] was promoted to President of the Flyers and [[Ron Hextall]] was promoted to General Manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flyers.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=718273|title=FLYERS PROMOTE PAUL HOLMGREN TO PRESIDENT; RON HEXTALL TO GENERAL MANAGER |publisher=Philadelphia Flyers|date=May 7, 2014|accessdate=May 7, 2014}}</ref>

On June 23, 2014, Hextall's first major move as General Manager was to trade [[Scott Hartnell]] to the [[Columbus Blue Jackets]] in exchange for [[R. J. Umberger]] and a fourth-round pick in the [[2015 NHL Entry Draft|2015 draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nhl/eye-on-hockey/24595134/scott-hartnell-traded-to-blue-jackets-for-rj-umberger-2015-pick|title=Scott Hartnell traded to Blue Jackets for R.J. Umberger, 2015 pick|publisher=cbssports.com|date=June 23, 2014|accessdate=November 29, 2014}}</ref> Hextall would later sign free agent defensemen [[Nick Schultz]] and [[Michael Del Zotto]] to one-year deals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=725229|title=Flyers sign Schultz, agree with Stortini|publisher=nhl.com|date=July 2, 2014|accessdate=November 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csnphilly.com/hockey-philadelphia-flyers/flyers-sign-michael-del-zotto-1-year-deal|title=Flyers sign Michael Del Zotto to 1-year deal|publisher=csnphilly.com|date=August 5, 2014|accessdate=November 29, 2014}}</ref>

