==Draft picks==
{{See also|List of Philadelphia Flyers draft picks}}

Below are the Philadelphia Flyers' selections made at the [[2014 NHL Entry Draft]], held on June 27–28, 2014 at the [[Wells Fargo Center (Philadelphia)|Wells Fargo Center]] in [[Philadelphia|Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://hockeydb.com/ihdb/draft/nhl2014e.html | title = 2014 NHL Entry Draft Picks at hockeydb.com | publisher = hockeyDB.com | accessdate = June 28, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NHL Entry Draft Year by Year Results|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/draftsearch.htm?year=2014&team=PHI&position=&round=|publisher=NHL.com|accessdate=June 28, 2014}}</ref><ref>http://www.litterboxcats.com/2014/4/15/5618872/panther-win-panthers-win-the-draft-lottery-that-is</ref> The team finished the previous season ranked 13th in the league, but secured the 17th overall pick, ahead of the [[New Jersey Devils]] who were relegated to the 30th spot for attempting to circumvent the salary cap in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Jersey Devils won't have to forfeit first-round pick over Ilya Kovalchuk deal, NHL announces|url=http://sports.nationalpost.com/2014/03/06/new-jersey-devils-wont-have-to-forfeit-first-round-pick-over-ilya-kovalchuk-deal-nhl-announces/|publisher=[[National Post]]|work=[[Associated Press|AP]]|date=March 6, 2014|accessdate=May 12, 2014|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140417035925/http://sports.nationalpost.com/2014/03/06/new-jersey-devils-wont-have-to-forfeit-first-round-pick-over-ilya-kovalchuk-deal-nhl-announces/|archive-date=April 17, 2014|dead-url=yes|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Flyers original third and fourth-round picks were traded to [[New York Islanders]] in two separate trades.<ref name="draftnotes">{{cite web|title=2014 NHL Entry Draft Pending Transactions|url=http://www.prosportstransactions.com/hockey/DraftTrades/Years/2014.htm|publisher=''Pro Sports Transactions''|accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref>

